---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
const pageTitle = "Privacy Policy – Simple Notes Sync | dettmer.dev";
const description =
  "Privacy Policy for the Android app Simple Notes Sync by Fabian Dettmer.";
---

<Layout pageTitle={pageTitle} description={description}>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="legal__lead">
    Privacy Policy for the Android app <strong>Simple Notes Sync</strong>
    (Package name: <code>dev.dettmer.simplenotes</code>), developed by Fabian Dettmer.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Responsible Party</h2>
  <p class="legal__block">
    Fabian Dettmer<br />
    Email: <a class="legal__link" href="mailto:admin@dettmer.dev">admin@dettmer.dev</a>
  </p>

  <h2>2. Principle: No Data Collection by the Developer</h2>
  <p class="legal__block">
    Simple Notes Sync does not collect, store, process, or transmit any personal data
    to the developer or third parties. The app contains no analytics libraries,
    tracking SDKs, advertising networks, or crash reporting services.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Local Data Storage</h2>
  <p class="legal__block">
    All notes are stored exclusively on the user's device. The developer has no access
    to this data.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Synchronization (WebDAV)</h2>
  <p class="legal__block">
    The app offers optional synchronization via the WebDAV protocol. The user configures
    their own WebDAV server of choice (e.&nbsp;g., a self-hosted server or a service like
    Nextcloud). The connection is established exclusively between the user's device and
    the server chosen by the user. The developer has no access to this connection or the
    transmitted data at any time.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Internet Permission</h2>
  <p class="legal__block">
    The app requires the <code>INTERNET</code> permission to perform optional WebDAV
    synchronization. This permission is used exclusively for the connection to the
    user-configured server. There is no communication with the developer's servers.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Local Backup</h2>
  <p class="legal__block">
    The app offers optional export and import functionality (JSON file, optionally
    encrypted). This data leaves the device only if the user actively exports it and
    shares it themselves.
  </p>

  <h2>7. No Sharing with Third Parties</h2>
  <p class="legal__block">
    Since no data is collected, no data is shared with third parties.
  </p>

  <h2>8. User Rights</h2>
  <p class="legal__block">
    Since the developer does not process any personal data, there are no data protection
    rights for information, correction, or deletion claims in relation to the developer.
    Inquiries can nevertheless be directed at any time by email to
    <a class="legal__link" href="mailto:admin@dettmer.dev">admin@dettmer.dev</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Open Source</h2>
  <p class="legal__block">
    Simple Notes Sync is free and open-source software (License: AGPL-3.0). The complete
    source code is available at:
    <a
      class="legal__link"
      href="https://github.com/inventory69/simple-notes-sync"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >github.com/inventory69/simple-notes-sync</a
    >.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
  <p class="legal__block">
    This Privacy Policy may be updated if there are material changes to the app.
    The date of the last update is provided below.
  </p>

  <p class="legal__block">
    <small>Last updated: April 2026</small>
  </p>
</Layout>
